<row>
<entry valign="top" align="left" namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Unit 3 Essay Activity</emphasis><newline/>
<emphasis effect="bold">Was the early republic truly an Era of Good Feelings?</emphasis><newline/>
<emphasis effect="bold">Option A: Evaluate the extent to which the Era of Good Feelings was a change from the founding spirit of the United States. In your response, consider the concepts of nationalism and sectionalism.</emphasis><newline/>
Through this inquiry, students will evaluate primary and secondary sources to evaluate the title traditionally given to the period of 1816 to 1824, the Era of Good Feelings. Students will evaluate this title through the lenses of various groups of Americans, political and social growth and conflict, and the U.S. role in the world. Assess students‚Äô progress in understanding the compelling question for this chapter by assigning the <link class="target-chapter" document="m78863">Unit 3 Essay Activity</link>.</entry>
</row>
